-- Gerry Weber Raises Sales Forecast, Sees `Disproportionate' Earnings Gain
-- B y   M i k e   G a v i n
-- 2010-11-05T08:05:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-05/gerry-weber-raises-sales-forecast-sees-disproportionate-earnings-gain.html
Gerry Weber International AG raised
its sales forecast for fiscal year 2010/11, which it said has
just started, to 685 million euros from 660 million euros. The
company again “projects a disproportionate increase in
earnings,” it said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
